/*
 mental cheat sheet
When writing methods:
Read-only operation:

Example:

size()
empty()
capacity()
begin()

Usually:

something() const;
Returning modifiable access:

Example:

T& operator[](int);
T& front();
T& back();
T* begin();

No const.

Returning read-only access:

Add overload:

const T& operator[](int) const;
const T& front() const;
const T* begin() const;

A good rule:

If the caller has a const object, every function they call must also be const.

And:

If you want the caller to modify the returned object, don't return const.
*/
